Riaan Grobler The house in Pretoria where a man was electrocuted while replacing a geyser.  (Netcare 911) Multimedia    ·   User Galleries   ·   News in Pictures
	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories A man was electrocuted while replacing a geyser in Mooikloof, Pretoria, on Tuesday afternoon. Netcare 911 said in a statement that the 22-year-old man's body had to be removed through the roof of the house he was working at. "The patient was assessed and found to sadly have no signs of life and declared deceased," spokesperson Shawn Herbst said. "The fire and rescue services had to be called to remove the deceased from the ceiling." All necessary authorities were on the scene, according to the statement.   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  